    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-15T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-15T03:00:00-05:00" n="643"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/154</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-15T09:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1918, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 16, 5.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2851. Zurich paper today contains interview with Turkish Minister at Berne. He
                    promises Switzerland that Turkey will open Dardanelles for wheat shipments
                    destined from Odessa to Switzerland. Before the war Switzerland’s main wheat
                    supply was obtained from Odessa. Heavy demands made upon United States since the
                    war are due to fact that this source of supply [has until] recently <pb
                        facs="0771" n="1605" xml:id="pg_1605"/> been closed to Switzerland. In this
                    connection prompt action of United States to retrieve Swiss cereal situation
                    vitally important and worth all the propaganda which we can throw into
                    Switzerland at this time.</p>
                <p>Recent action of Wheat Executive in London liable to delay shipments of wheat to
                    Switzerland for a long time.</p>
                <p>I have communicated substance of your 1604, March 12, to Swiss Government, which
                    welcomes it with satisfaction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
